# Database — Remote Only

This project uses Cloudflare D1 as its database. There is **no local database** — both development and production connect to the **remote** D1 instance.

## Rules

- **NEVER** use `--local` flag with `wrangler d1` commands. Always use `--remote`.
- The `wrangler.json` D1 binding has `"remote": true` — do not change this.
- When running seeds, migrations, or queries via `wrangler d1 execute`, always pass `--remote`.
- Do not reference or rely on `.wrangler/state/` local SQLite files — they are stale/unused.

## Examples

```bash
# ✅ CORRECT
npx wrangler d1 execute champty-db --remote --file drizzle/seed.sql
npx wrangler d1 execute champty-db --remote --command "SELECT * FROM templates;"
npx wrangler d1 migrations apply champty-db --remote

# ❌ WRONG — never use --local
npx wrangler d1 execute champty-db --local --file drizzle/seed.sql
npx wrangler d1 execute champty-db --command "SELECT * FROM templates;"  # missing --remote
```
